<p>
This website is part of the SenseSourcing project in the 
<a target="_blank" href="http://scc.lancs.ac.uk/">School of Computing and Communications</a> at 
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.lancaster.ac.uk/">Lancaster University</a>, UK. The SenseSourcing project is using crowdsourcing methods to collect expert and non-expert manual judgements and classifications of the meanings of words in a variety of languages. These manual classifications (tags) will help us to improve the semantic dictionaries for the 
<a target="_blank" href="http://ucrel.lancs.ac.uk/usas/">USAS (UCREL Semantic Analysis System) tagger</a> which is an automatic software system for the semantic analysis of language. 
</p><p>
The SenseSourcing project was funded by an EPSRC Impact Acceleration Award to
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.comp.lancs.ac.uk/~paul/">Dr Paul Rayson</a> in 2013/14 which provided resources for development work and a literature survey by 
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.extremetomato.com/">Steve Wattam</a>. The 
<a target="_blank" href="http://ucrel.lancs.ac.uk/">UCREL research centre</a> funded further research, development and dissemination by <a target="_blank" href="http://www.lancaster.ac.uk/staff/elhaj/">Dr Mahmoud El-Haj</a> in 2015. 
This research is carried out in collaboration with the ESRC-funded
<a target="_blank" href="http://cass.lancs.ac.uk/">Centre for Corpus Approaches to Social Science</a>.
</p><p>
The tags presented through this website result from an initial draft semantic dictionary for a language derived from an automatic 'translation' process. Due to the inevitable ambiguity of translations and part-of-speech correspondence across and between languages, the automatically translated lexicons contain errors, which need to be cleaned manually. 
In order to reference this further development of the multilingual USAS tagger, please cite our paper at NAACL-HLT 2015:
</p><p>

<a target="_blank" href="http://ucrel.lancs.ac.uk/publications/piaoEtAl_NAACL2015.pdf">Piao, S., Bianchi, F., Dayrell, C., D'Egidio, A. and Rayson, P. (2015). 
Development of the multilingual semantic annotation system. 
In proceedings of the 2015 Conference of the North American Chapter of the 
Association for Computational Linguistics - Human Language Technologies 
(NAACL HLT 2015), Denver, Colorado, United States.</a></p>
